cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically object skeleton detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves optimizing the reconstruction error of the network, suggesting that it could also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper utilizes subspace linear span to increase the efficiency of feature integration, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, indicating that it could also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
